### isDeInterleaveMask() {#a1197fc4e7554381767b15551de4f9334}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool isDeInterleaveMask (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef</a>&lt; int &gt; Mask, unsigned &amp; Factor, unsigned &amp; Index, unsigned MaxFactor, unsigned NumLoadElements)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/check">Check</a> if the mask is a DE-interleave mask for an interleaved load.

E.g. DE-interleave masks (Factor = 2) could be: &lt;0, 2, 4, 6&gt; (mask of index 0 to extract even elements) &lt;1, 3, 5, 7&gt; (mask of index 1 to extract odd elements)

Definition at line <a href="#l00208">208</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/interleavedaccesspass-cpp">InterleavedAccessPass.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

### isReInterleaveMask() {#aa5abbc18f35b5384a55bfd244064493d}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool isReInterleaveMask (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/shufflevectorinst">ShuffleVectorInst</a> &#42; SVI, unsigned &amp; Factor, unsigned MaxFactor)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
<a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/check">Check</a> if the mask can be used in an interleaved store.

It checks for a more general pattern than the RE-interleave mask. I.e. &lt;x, y, ... z, x+1, y+1, ...z+1, x+2, y+2, ...z+2, ...&gt; E.g. For a Factor of 2 (LaneLen=4): &lt;4, 32, 5, 33, 6, 34, 7, 35&gt; E.g. For a Factor of 3 (LaneLen=4): &lt;4, 32, 16, 5, 33, 17, 6, 34, 18, 7, 35, 19&gt; E.g. For a Factor of 4 (LaneLen=2): &lt;8, 2, 12, 4, 9, 3, 13, 5&gt;

The particular case of an RE-interleave mask is: I.e. &lt;0, LaneLen, ... , LaneLen&#42;(Factor - 1), 1, LaneLen + 1, ...&gt; E.g. For a Factor of 2 (LaneLen=4): &lt;0, 4, 1, 5, 2, 6, 3, 7&gt;

Definition at line <a href="#l00237">237</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/interleavedaccesspass-cpp">InterleavedAccessPass.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>

<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// DE-interleaving the data on a factor. An interleaved store writes several</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00020" /><CodeLine lineNumber="20"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// intrinsics can be easily matched into target specific instructions later in</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="203"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Check if the mask is a DE-interleave mask for an interleaved load.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="204"><Highlight kind="comment">///</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="205"><Highlight kind="comment">/// E.g. DE-interleave masks (Factor = 2) could be:</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="206"><Highlight kind="comment">///     &lt;0, 2, 4, 6&gt;    (mask of index 0 to extract even elements)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="207"><Highlight kind="comment">///     &lt;1, 3, 5, 7&gt;    (mask of index 1 to extract odd elements)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="208" lineLink="#a1197fc4e7554381767b15551de4f9334"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">static</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">bool</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> <a href="#a1197fc4e7554381767b15551de4f9334">isDeInterleaveMask</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/arrayref">ArrayRef&lt;int&gt;</a> Mask, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &amp;Factor,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="209"><Highlight kind="normal">                               </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> &amp;Index, </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> MaxFactor,</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="210"><Highlight kind="normal">                               </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordtype">unsigned</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> NumLoadElements) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="211"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">if</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (Mask.size() &lt; 2)</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="212"><Highlight kind="normal">    </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">return</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> </Highlight><Highlight kind="keyword">false</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal">;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="215"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="keywordflow">for</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"> (Factor = 2; Factor &lt;= MaxFactor; Factor++) &#123;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00226" /><CodeLine lineNumber="226"><Highlight kind="comment">/// Check if the mask can be used in an interleaved store.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00228" /><CodeLine lineNumber="228"><Highlight kind="comment">/// It checks for a more general pattern than the RE-interleave mask.</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00229" /><CodeLine lineNumber="229"><Highlight kind="comment">/// I.e. &lt;x, y, ... z, x+1, y+1, ...z+1, x+2, y+2, ...z+2, ...&gt;</Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00481" /><CodeLine lineNumber="481"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00482" /><CodeLine lineNumber="482"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// For an (de)interleave tree like this:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00483" /><CodeLine lineNumber="483"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00484" /><CodeLine lineNumber="484"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   A   C B   D</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00485" /><CodeLine lineNumber="485"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   |&#95;&#95;&#95;| |&#95;&#95;&#95;|</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00486" /><CodeLine lineNumber="486"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//     |&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;&#95;|</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00487" /><CodeLine lineNumber="487"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//        |</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00488" /><CodeLine lineNumber="488"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//     A B C D</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00489" /><CodeLine lineNumber="489"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00490" /><CodeLine lineNumber="490"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  We will get ABCD at the end while the leaf operands/results</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00491" /><CodeLine lineNumber="491"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  are ACBD, which are also what we initially collected in</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00492" /><CodeLine lineNumber="492"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  getVectorInterleaveFactor / getVectorDeinterleaveFactor. But TLI</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00493" /><CodeLine lineNumber="493"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  hooks (e.g. lowerDeinterleaveIntrinsicToLoad) expect ABCD, so we need</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
